  {
    "block_id": "doxcnh0MhFIUW40vv8jzckKFIKb",
    "block_type": 2,
    "parent_id": "SWuAdfxPHoDRD3x9i0JcqmConEc",
    "text": {
      "elements": [
        {
          "text_run": {
            "content": "RAG / digest workflows commonly need to summarise a Feishu doc. The structured JSON returned by get_doc_blocks is rich (block ids, parent links, style metadata) but consumes ~2x more tokens than a Markdown rendering for the same semantic content. The new read_doc_markdown tool wraps feishu-docx::transform() and post-processes the output so embedded images and files are surfaced as feishu://image_token/<TOKEN> placeholders that the agent can dereference with download_doc_image when it actually needs the binary. For agents that only need text understanding (which is the common case), this is pure savings — typical ratio measured at 30-50%, target ≥58% reduction.",
            "text_element_style": {
              "bold": false,
              "inline_code": false,
              "italic": false,
              "strikethrough": false,
              "underline": false
            }
          }
        }
      ],
      "style": {
        "align": 1,
        "folded": false
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "block_id": "doxcnhpJXQafiDSRg7POXzK1vmb",
    "block_type": 2,
    "parent_id": "SWuAdfxPHoDRD3x9i0JcqmConEc",
    "text": {
      "elements": [
        {
          "text_run": {
            "content": "A second paragraph reinforcing volume so the markdown/json ratio measurement isn't dominated by metadata overhead from a single small block. Lorem ipsum filler is fine here, but real content gives a more honest read on whitespace and inline-style overhead. The probe script measures len(JSON.stringify(blocks)) vs len(transform(blocks)) and prints the ratio.",
            "text_element_style": {
              "bold": false,
              "inline_code": false,
              "italic": false,
              "strikethrough": false,
              "underline": false
            }
          }
        }
      ],
      "style": {
        "align": 1,
        "folded": false
      }
    }
  },
